  <title>Scottish CROP Research Institute:Strengthening Potato Production</title>
  <description>An earlier survey by the Scottish Crop Research Institute (SCRI) identified practical interventions with the potential to improve the Malawian potato crop. This project addresses some of the issues identified within the survey and has the overall aim of contributing to poverty reduction through strengthening the development of sustainable potato production and marketing systems for improved productivity and trade. Key activities are the training of crop inspectors, extension workers, specialist seed growers and potato farmers; the development of field multiplication sites for dry and rainy season production; and the demonstration of best practice in potato production.</description>
